[1
Date: Thu, 8 Jul 1999 01:04:30 -0700 (PDT)
From: Loiosh <loiosh@redplanetsw.com>
Source: <http://www.rgj.com/news/stories/reno/931323180.html>

The Washoe County Health Department [Nevada has issued a recall on Sun
Orchards non- pasteurized orange juices sold under the names Sun Orchard,
Trader Joe's, Aloha, Zupan and Voila. This comes after two people have been
confirmed as having [disease caused by _Salmonella muenchen_ , and another
two cases are awaiting laboratory confirmation.
--
Kelly Hills
e-mail: loiosh@redplanetsw.com
*********
[2
Date: Thu, 08 Jul 1999 09:06:48 -0700
From: Emilio E DEBESS <Emilio_E_DEBESS@ohdmail.hr.state.or.us>
So far 40 cases of _S. Muenchen_ [infection have been confirmed at the
Oregon Public Health Laboratory. There are about 20 _Salmonella_ of unknown
serotype pending at the laboratory. Most have had the implicated orange
juice. For more information regarding age groups and counties including an
Epi-curve visit our web site at
<http://www.ohd.hr.state.or.us/cdpe/acd/outbreak/home.htm>
--
Emilio DeBess, DVM, MPVM.
Oregon Health Division
e-mail: Emilio_E_DEBESS@ohdmail.hr.state.or.us
